  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      CARMEN is a clinical registry of all incident adult Immune thrombocytopenia (ITP) and
      Autoimmune Hemolytic anemia (AIHA) patients in the Midi-Pyrenees region (South of France). It
      is aimed at describing ITP and AIHA clinical features, assessing the risk-benefit ratio of
      second-line treatments (SLTs) and adherence to guidelines for ITP and AIHA management.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
