  <eligibility>
    <study_pop>
      <textblock>
        Adult ITP and AIHA case recording in the Midi-Pyrénées region, South of France. ITP
        patients are treated by internal medicine and hematology practitioners actually spread in
        one tertiary hospital (located in Toulouse and including one hematology and six internal
        medicine departments) and 14 peripheral public or private hospitals. All these
        practitioners take actively part to the network of the Midi-Pyrénées Competence Center for
        Autoimmune Cytopenias.
      </textblock>
    </study_pop>
    <sampling_method>Non-Probability Sample</sampling_method>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  More than 18 years

          -  newly diagnosed ITP or AIHA
      </textblock>
